The problem of opportunity - model outputs

Jonathan R Goodman

#Basic Prisoner's Dilemma: no punishment; cooperators and defectors are unconditional

basic.output <- basic.PD(generations=10e3, mu=.01, delta=.0) 
#plot outputs

library(ggplot2)

#relative frequency of cooperators vs defectors over generations

PD.frequency(basic.output[[1]])


#overall percentage of of cooperative behaviours over generations

coop.frequency(basic.output[[2]])

PD.frequency(mimic.model1.output[[1]], every = 1000)

coop.frequency(mimic.model1.output[[4]], every = 1000)

#create a single data frame amalgamating defector strategy, mimic type, and silent appearance in Model 3

model3.output.d <- mimic.novel.PD.output[[1]][mimic.novel.PD.output[[1]]$strategy=="d",]
model3.output.m <- mimic.novel.PD.output[[2]][mimic.novel.PD.output[[2]]$type=="m",]
model3.output.s <- mimic.novel.PD.output[[3]][mimic.novel.PD.output[[3]]$appearance=="s",]

names(model3.output.d)[names(model3.output.d)=="strategy"] <- "quality"
names(model3.output.m)[names(model3.output.m)=="type"] <- "quality"
names(model3.output.s)[names(model3.output.s)=="appearance"] <- "quality"

model3.outputs.quality <- rbind(model3.output.d,model3.output.m,model3.output.s)

#plot by every 1,000 generations

 defector <- seq(1,nrow(model3.outputs.quality),1000)
 mimic <- seq(2,nrow(model3.outputs.quality),1000)
 silent <- seq(3,nrow(model3.outputs.quality),1000)
 
 data.every <- c(defector,mimic,silent)
 data.every <- sort(data.every)
  
  ggplot(data=model3.outputs.quality[data.every,], aes(x=generation,y=Freq, color=quality))+
  geom_line(alpha=0.6)+
  scale_color_manual(values=c("red","orange","black"), labels=c("defector","mimic","silent"))+labs(y="frequency")+theme_bw()


#sensitivity probability model
